{{Infobox French canton |name=[[Cantons of France|Canton]] of Monthureux-sur-Saône |reg=[[Lorraine (region)|Lorraine]] |dept=[[Vosges (department)|Vosges]] |arr= |numcomm=11 |cancode=88 17 |pop=2614 |year=1999 |area=139.21 }} The '''Canton of Monthureux-sur-Saône''' is a former [[Cantons of France|French administrative and electoral grouping of communes]] in the [[Vosges (department)|Vosges]] ''[[departments of France|département]]'' of eastern [[France]] and in the [[Regions of France|region]] of [[Lorraine (region)|Lorraine]]. It was disbanded following the French canton reorganisation which came into effect in March 2015. It consisted of 11 communes, which joined the [[canton of Darney]] in 2015.<ref>[http://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/affichTexte.do?cidTexte=JORFTEXT000028664666 Décret n° 2014-268 du 27 février 2014 portant délimitation des cantons dans le département des Vosges]</ref>
One of 15 cantons in the [[Arrondissement of Épinal]], the Canton of Monthureux-sur-Saône had its administrative centre at [[Monthureux-sur-Saône]].
==Composition== The Canton of Monthureux-sur-Saône comprised the following 11 [[Communes of France|communes]] : *[[Ameuvelle]] *[[Bleurville]] *[[Claudon]] *[[Fignévelle]] *[[Gignéville]] *[[Godoncourt]] *[[Martinvelle]] *[[Monthureux-sur-Saône]] *[[Nonville, Vosges|Nonville]] *[[Regnévelle]] *[[Viviers-le-Gras]]
The [[Degree Confluence Project|intersection]] of the [[48th parallel north]] with the [[6th meridian east]] of [[Prime Meridian|Greenwich]] occurs in the canton, within the commune of [[Martinvelle]].
