{{Infobox coat of arms |name = Coat of arms of Kumanovo |image = File:Coat of arms of Kumanovo Municipality.svg |alt = |image_width = 150 |middle = |middle_width = |middle_caption = |lesser = |lesser_alt = |lesser_width = |lesser_caption = |image2 = File:MMCA Kumanovo.png |image2_alt = |image2_width = |image2_caption = Version with single green tobacco leaf |image3 = |image3_alt = |image3_width = |image3_caption = |armiger = none |year_adopted = 1996 |crest = none |torse = none |shield = Spanish |supporter =none |supporters = none |compartment = |motto = |orders = |badge =none |other_elements = |earlier_versions = |use = On Flag of Kumanovo |notes = }}
The '''coat of arms of Kumanovo ''' is actually an emblem. Milosh Kostadinov in 1970 wrote an article on [[municipal heraldry]] and came to the conclusion that just seven municipalities in the [[Socialist Republic of Macedonia]] used a [[coat of arms]],<ref>[http://heraldika.org.mk/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/MkHerald-6.pdf Macedonian Herald, Issue 6, p.4] "Heraldika"; retrieved 28 January 2017</ref> one of which was [[Kumanovo Municipality|Kumanovo]]. The coat of arms has been changed since Macedonian independence from the former [[Yugoslavia]].
In 2012 Jovan Jovanovski of the Macedonian Heraldic Society has described the current coat of arms as both "non-heraldic" and "quasi-heraldic".<ref>[http://heraldika.org.mk/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/MkHerald-6.pdf Macedonian Herald, Issue 6, p.9 & p.31] "Heraldika"; retrieved 28 January 2017</ref> The Kumanovo coat of arms is placed on a so-called [[Spanish heraldry#Heraldic regulation|Spanish shield]].<ref>[http://heraldika.org.mk/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/mkherald-8.pdf Macedonian Herald, Issue 8, p.7] "Heraldika"; retrieved 28 January 2017</ref> The shield depicts a building (the ''Zanaetchiski dom''), a statue of a woman from the [[Memorial Ossuary Kumanovo]], a yellow sun, the year 1519 (when the name Kumanovo was found in a Turkish document), the name of the town in Cyrillic script and at the bottom a single yellow tobacco leaf, all against a red background.
