'''Foreign Literature Committee''' ({{lang-ru|Комитет иностранной литературы}}), or '''Kominolit''' ({{lang-ru|Коминолит}}), was an interdepartmental committee under the [[Government of the Soviet Union|People's Commissariat]] for Education for the purchase and distribution of foreign literature in [[Russian SFSR|Soviet Russia]]. Its chairman as of October 1921 was [[Otto Yulyevich Schmidt]].<ref>[http://www.marxists.org/archive/lenin/works/1921/sep/30d.htm Lenin: 414. TO THE FOREIGN LITERATURE COMMITTEE<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

