{{other uses|Mata Hari (disambiguation)}} {{unreferenced|date=September 2013}} {{Infobox song contest entry | song = {{flagicon|Norway}} "Mata Hari" | image = [[File:Mata_Hari_(song).jpg|250 px]] | caption = | year = 1976 | country = Norway | artist = Anne Karine Strøm | as = | with = | language = English | languages = | composer = [[Frode Thingnæs]] | lyricist = Philip A. Kruse | conductor = [[Frode Thingnæs]] | place = 18th | points = 7 | lyrics = [http://www.diggiloo.net/?1976no from Diggiloo Thrush] | prev = Touch My Life (With Summer) | prev_link = Touch My Life (With Summer) | next = Casanova | next_link = Casanova (Anita Skorgan song) }}
'''"Mata Hari"''' was the [[Norway|Norwegian]] entry in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1976]], performed in [[English language|English]] by [[Anne-Karine Strøm]].
The song is an up-tempo number, in which Strøm sings about the difficulties she faces in life. The cure for these, she sings, is to borrow some of the mystique of [[Mata Hari]], to whom she addresses the song. The sexual exploits of the famous woman are implied to have been considerable.
The song was performed ninth on the night, following the [[Netherlands]]' [[Sandra Reemer]] with "[[The Party's Over (Sandra Reemer song)|The Party's Over]]" and preceding [[Greece]]'s [[Mariza Koch]] with "[[Panayia Mu, Panayia Mu]]". At the close of voting, it had received 7 points, placing 18th (last) in a field of 18.
Strøm had represented Norway at Eurovision twice before, once in [[Eurovision Song Contest 1973|1973]] as part of vocal group The Bendik Singers and again as a solo performer in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1974|1974 Contest]].
As of 2012, Strøm still holds the record as the only artist in the history of Eurovision to have finished in last place twice. The first time came in 1974 with the song "[[The First Day of Love]]".
Anne was succeeded as [[Norway in the Eurovision Song Contest|Norwegian representative]] at the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1977|1977 contest]] by [[Anita Skorgan]] with "[[Casanova (Anita Skorgan song)|Casanova]]".
