The '''Order of the Croatian Interlace''' or '''Order of the Early Croatian three-strand pattern''' ({{lang-hr|Red hrvatskog pletera}}) is the sixteenth most important medal given by the [[Republic of Croatia]]. The order was founded on April 1, 1995. The medal is awarded for advancement of progress and reputation of Croatia and the welfare of its citizens.<ref>{{cite journal | url = http://www.nn.hr/clanci/sluzbeno/1995/0377.htm | journal = [[Narodne novine]] | issue = 1995/20 | author = [[Croatian Parliament]] | language = Croatian | title = Zakon o odlikovanjima i priznanjima Republike Hrvatske | date = 1995-03-24 | accessdate = 2011-11-16}}</ref> It is named after the [[Croatian Interlace]], a traditional Croatian ornamental design, an interwoven series of branches used as a wall or barrier.

