{{ infobox person | name = Philippe Crouzet | image = Philippe-Crouzet.jpg | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1956|10|18|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Neuilly-sur-Seine]], [[France]] | nationality = [[France|French]] | education = [[Lycée Pasteur (Neuilly-sur-Seine)|Lycée Pasteur]] | alma_mater = [[Sciences Po]], [[École nationale d'administration|ÉNA]] | occupation = CEO of [[Vallourec]] | spouse = {{marriage|[[Sylvie Hubac]]|19 December 1983}} }}
'''Philippe Crouzet''' (born 18 October 1956 in [[Neuilly-sur-Seine]]) is a [[France|French]] businessman, and the chairman of the management board of [[Vallourec]] ({{Euronext|VK}}) since April 2009.<ref>(fr) [http://www.edubourse.com/biographie/philippe-crouzet.php Biographie Philippe Crouzet], ''Edubourse''</ref>
==Biography== ===Early life=== Philippe Crouzet graduated from [[Sciences Po]] in 1976 and the [[École nationale d'administration]] in 1981.<ref name="businessweek">[http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/people/person.asp?personId=7768410&ticker=VK:FP&previousCapId=874654&previousTitle=VALLOUREC Bloomberg BusinessWeek]</ref><ref name="vallourec">[http://www.vallourec.com/en/group/news/NewsDetail.aspx?NewsID=3&List=News%20List Vallourec]</ref>
===Career=== He served as counsel (Maître des requêtes) to the [[Conseil d'Etat (France)|Conseil d'Etat]].<ref name="vallourec"/>
In 1986, he joined [[Saint-Gobain]] ({{Euronext|SGO}}) as director of corporate planning. Three years later, in 1989, he was appointed general manager of the paper business unit (Papeteries de Condat). From 1992 to 1996, he was a general delegate for Spain and Portugal, and then CEO of the ceramics division until 2000.<ref name="businessweek"/><ref name="vallourec"/> He later served as Senior Vice-President of the Group in charge of Finance, Purchasing and Information Systems.<ref name="vallourec"/> From 2005 to 2009, he served as Senior Vice-President in charge of the building distribution sector.<ref name="vallourec"/>
===Personal life and interests=== He is married to [[Sylvie Hubac]], who has served as the Chief of Staff of President [[François Hollande]] since 2012.
Philippe Crouzet is the founder and president of ARES, an association specialized in professional reinsertion of socially impaired persons in the [[Île-de-France]] area.<ref>[http://corporate-executives.com/philippe-crouzet/ Biography Philippe Crouzet], ''Corporate Executives''</ref>
