{{Infobox law enforcement agency |agencyname = Moldovan Carabinier Troops |nativename = Trupele de Carabinieri |patch = CoATrupeCarabinieri.png |patchcaption = Coat of Arms of the Moldovan Carabinier Troops |imagesize = 150 |formedyear = 12 December 1991 |gendarmerie = Yes |national = Yes |country = Republic of Moldova |legaljuris = opsjuris |headquarters = Chişinău |chief1name = Veaceslav Ceban |chief1position = Comandant |website = [http://www.carabinier.gov.md] |narrowerbox = Yes }}
'''''Trupele de Carabinieri''''' ([[Carabinier]] Troops) is the [[gendarmerie]]-type force of the [[Ministry of Internal Affairs (Moldova)|Ministry of Internal Affairs of Moldova]]. The Moldovan Carabinieri are to ensure, together with the police or independently, public order, protection of rights and freedoms of citizens, owners' properties and prevention of violations of the law.The Department of Carabineer Troops has 5 Military Units and some 2,000 soldiers working on a contract basis or on time. On December 12, 1991, the establishment of the Carabinieri Troops was approved by the Parliament and subsequently signed by the President of the Republic of Moldova.<ref>http://mai.gov.md/ro/content/departamentul-trupelor-de-carabinieri-26-de-ani-de-la-fondare</ref>
